commit.message:
Reformat the rdoc so it renders correctly both locally and on github.

The current formatting (esp code blocks) looks bad on github and just
stops before the first code block locally.

Allow racc cmdline to read from stdin if no path specified.

This requires the use of -o <path> to specify where to write but
should allow for piping to racc:

    preprocess_cmd | racc -o lib/parser.rb

commit.message:
'lib/racc/parser-text.rb' depends on 'lib/racc/info.rb'

In the rake task, `require 'racc/info'` is expanded to actual file
contents. Then 'lib/racc/parser-text.rb' depends on 'lib/racc/info.rb'.

commit.message:
Check `rake build` on CI

Sometimes `rake build` is broken. For example in v1.7.2, mismatch
of "cparse-jruby.jar" path between racc.gemspec and Rakefile
makes `rake build` failed.
Add a check on CI to detect such problem in advance.
